 of\nCalifornia. She came to this city in\n1900 and became, in 1901, a member\nof the old Tech faculty. The work\nof arranging English classes at the\nschool to accommodate the crowded\nenrollment of recent years had put\nher under a mental strain, and.\nthreatened with a nervous breakdown.\nshe secured leave of absence\nfor a year last September, going to\nher old home in California. Derailed\ninformation with regard to her death\nand funeral has not reached this'city.\ne*,\nDr. W. C. Rodger* Dead.\nPHILADELPHIA.?The Rev. Dr. William\nCunningham Rodgers, rector of Old\nSt. David's Protestant Episcopal Church\nat Radnor, near here, is dead at his\nhome here. He was sixty-four years\nold. Dr. Rodgers was editor-in-chief of\nthe Church News of the Pennsylvania\nDiocese. He had served parishes at\nWilkinsburg, Pa.: Davenport. Iowa;\nGloversville. Hoosick Falls and Millbrook.\nN. Y.\ni dnm\nfifty years our prices have b<\ntoday.\n\nHIS I\ni Over- \"Opp\n4 IT n 4 4-Vi A\numi uic\nlick is l^ii\nctions.\n:o sen-\na to-\nmuck Crompton\nduroy snits,\nV tkat Wood Br\ny iHdi Wltjj two pi\n\"L __r_ Fancy Chi\nnave one, others\n1 pants.\ntO de- Novelty\nbreasted, bu\nven US \"Kkinaw\nyears.\ny deep. i\n:k ex- AlSOBoys'\n10HS bocker, otl\n>ilities to 15 ytar\nBoys'\narage- are the sp<\nReduced ft\nBoys'\n-i sizes from\nitmgly\nBoys\nCrimi- fitting brai\nir\nf There\nkeeps hin\nThese\n17 1 *1\nA, M V-nec\nA f ?in Blue\ntures\nis\n>E\nCloth 1\nlined. $2\ney?but Thread\nothers Risi\n4\nWinter\npercentage\nRegular\n?r\nWe a\nin all the\nm? lined and\nothers boi\n:acturers All the\navorably Boys'\nare bar- fancy\n15-00\nA sele\n1 Q.75 Brow;n'1\nX ?7 popular\nRcgardle\nSo QS Boys.'\nsoles and i\nly* to 5 y2.\nE. E. RAMEY. D, C. REALTY\nBROKER. PIES IN HOSPITAL\n\nProminent Member of Board of\nTrade?Had Been 111 Since\nChristmas Night.\n^KfSnWs- )*A?\nf r SI\nMB?: jj^SnsSn^\njflfiSSnk\nK. F, RAMEV,.\nE. E. Ramey local real estate broker\nand prominent member of the Washington\nBoard of 