er reaching the hospital, before\nmidnight.\nMr. Ramey was chairman' of last\nyear's membership committee of the\nBoard of Trade. Under his leadership\nthe courmtttee established a record\nfor obtaining new members, fpr\nwhich Work'he was feted at a dinner\nrecently given by the present membership\nCommittee. He was to have\nbeen the guest of honor at the annual\nmembership 1> flq t of-th- Hoard\nof Trade, at the Wii'ard the 22d of this\nmonth. I\nHe was born in Indiana county. Pa., i\ntifty-nine years ago. and had lived\nIn Washington most of his life. He\nwas a member of Harmony Hodge.\nNo. 17. P. A. A. M.\nH#? is swrvlv fl by w^ov\\ i\nLillian Ttarrey: a son. Pflul-G. Ramey,'\nand a daughter. J->ne Gould Barney.\nPur.eral services will be held Sunday\nnfterr'-n- 2 o'c!o?'< in the\nchapel of T' o Ser-eou's u-'der-\ntaking establ-sh-Tent. 1111 7th street j\nnorthwest. Masonic services a ill he j\nconducted at the g-ave. Interment j\nwill be in Rock Creek cemetery. j\nASK DRY LAW CHANGES.\nMeasures Introduced in California\n\nLegislature.\nSACRA VKNTO. Jauupary 7\nTwo measures memorializing Congress\nto permit the different states to\nfix the alcoholic content of beverages\nand to amend the Volstead act to per-\nmit manufacture of light wines and\nbeer have been introduced in- the California\nlegislature.\nif\nSeventh U\\\nStreet ii\nas any house\nmpany\nL!\nDing I\nem?so grouped jj;!\nice is liberalized. jj\nioice for\n12-75\nof Fancy Cheviot and j||j;\nSuits, with one and two jjijlj\npants?some are the II li\nfht Posture. |i|j!\n:s for school and\nir; neat fancy patterns'; hjj\niund. '!|j!\nOvercoats?in. Chinchilla U I\nT Mixtures; button to jjjii\nall around. <!il|\nws?convertible collars; jiljij\nsmart plaid combina\" i|ji|\nnc knicker- j|i;i\n:d: Sizcs4$J.48 jjjjj\nitures; they\n58^.0,11.5^49 I\nMl cut; 51^5\nA\nof the best 95c\ners\nup\" to a man and\nnntylvaniat\nPull-overs\nford mix- $8-75\nings\n:lasp;' wqo1: $1.15\ni f?\nciuckcu, anu (ljctc\nde- OO\nma.ke\